# Command Sender

Commands can be run by players OR console.

## Example
```java
if (!(sender instanceof Player)) {
    sender.sendMessage("Only players can use this!");
    return true;
}

Player player = (Player) sender;
player.sendMessage("Hello player!");
```

## Logic
- Check sender type
- Cast safely

## Edge Case
Console has no location or inventory.

# Arguments

Arguments are extra inputs after a command.

## Example
`/hello Steve`

```java
if (args.length > 0) {
    sender.sendMessage("Hello " + args[0]);
} else {
    sender.sendMessage("Hello!");
}
```

## Logic
- args[0] = first word
- Always check length first

## Edge Case
Accessing args[0] without checking causes errors.

# Tab Completion

## Example
```java
public class HelloTab implements TabCompleter {
    @Override
    public List<String> onTabComplete(CommandSender sender, Command command, String alias, String[] args) {
        if (args.length == 1) {
            return Arrays.asList("Steve", "Alex");
        }
        return Collections.emptyList();
    }
}
```

## Register
```java
getCommand("hello").setTabCompleter(new HelloTab());
```

## Logic
- Suggest options based on args length

# Subcommands

## Example
```java
if (args.length == 0) {
    sender.sendMessage("/hello reload");
    return true;
}

if (args[0].equalsIgnoreCase("reload")) {
    sender.sendMessage("Reloaded!");
}
```

## Logic
- args[0] decides action

## Expand
- /hello give
- /hello reload
- /hello info
